Summary:
1. **Primary Request and Intent:**

   The user gave a single directive to solve GitHub issue https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/issues/812 ("Check for all false positives, false negatives, warnings and errors in CI/CD and fix them all") in working directory `/tmp/gh-issue-solver-1784567326843`, on prepared branch `issue-812-7f9674a82402`, updating the already-existing PR https://github.com/link-assistant/formal-ai/pull/813.

   Explicit requirements from the user message:
   - "Download all logs and collect data related about the issue to this repository, and compile that data into the ./dev/log/issues/812/pulls/813 folder."
   - "Use the collected evidence to do a deep analysis (search online for additional facts and data), reconstruct the timeline/sequence of events, list each and every requirement from the issue, find the root cause of each problem, and propose possible solutions and solution plans for each requirement. Also check online for known existing components/libraries that solve a similar problem or can help."
   - "If there is not enough data to find the actual root cause, add debug output and a verbose mode (if not already present) so the root cause can be found on the next iteration. Keep the default state switched off."
   - "If the issue is related to another repository/project, report issues on GitHub for that project when possible. Each report must contain reproducible examples, workarounds, and suggestions for fixing the issue in code."
   - "Double-check that the requirements are fully applied to the entire codebase: if an issue exists in multiple places, apply it in all of them."

   Constraints stated in the environment/guidelines: push only to branch `issue-812-7f9674a82402`; PR 813 already exists (update, don't create); run local CI checks before pushing; commit atomic steps; use `gh pr ready 813` when finished; save large logs to files; read files >1500 lines in chunks; keep debug/test scripts in `./examples` and/or `./experiments`.

   The issue body itself adds requirements: compare against `link-foundation/{rust,js,python}-ai-driven-development-pipeline-template` (full file tree), report issues upstream in the templates if the same defect is found there, follow `https://github.com/link-assistant/hive-mind/blob/main/docs/CI-CD-BEST-PRACTICES.md`, and "plan and execute everything in this single pull request … until it is each and every requirement fully addressed".

2. **Key Technical Concepts:**
   - GitHub Actions CI/CD (`release.yml` = "CI/CD Pipeline", `desktop-release.yml` = "Desktop Release"), workflow_run triggers, job-level `if:`/`timeout-minutes`/concurrency/permissions
   - `rust-script` standalone scripts in `scripts/*.rs`, included into tests via `#[path = ...] mod`
